{
  "text": "As with stress, insufficient job control and decision latitude are associated with higher incidence of anxiety in the workplace, and other forms of mental distress [CITATION_1] . With the trend towards flatter organisational structures, the heightened level of responsibility imposed on most employees as middle management roles disappear may leave some employees feeling overwhelmed [CITATION_2] ). For employees who lack self-reliance, flatter organisational structures not only have the capacity to cause psychological distress, they can also result in a range of physical illnesses [CITATION_3] . For instance, it has been found that the greater an employee's responsibility and workload is, the more likely it is for that employee's immune system to be compromised which in turn has the capacity to make them more susceptible to upper respiratory illnesses such as colds and influenza (Shaubroeck et al. 2001 ).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "12534252",
    "[CITATION_2]": "12166527",
    "[CITATION_3]": "12166527"
